{{version030}}
{{flavour|Fires a penetrating bolt of acid.}}

'''Corrosive Bolt''' launches a piercing bolt of [[acid]] that does heavy damage and causes [[corrosion]]. It is largely used by monsters, though players may cast it using a [[wand of acid]].

{{monsters with spell}}

==History==
*In [[0.29]], monsters now deal less damage with Corrosive Bolt. Monsters with the spell were only slightly nerfed, but monsters with a wand of acid deal much less damage.
*Prior to [[0.28]], Corrosive Bolt did less base damage, but had extra "[[acid|acid splash]]" damage (4d5 against players, 2d4 against monsters).
*Wands of acid were added in [[0.18]].
*This spell was added in [[0.17]].

[[Category:Monster spells]]
